headline: Analysts See Domino's Pizza Stock As Too Cheap Ahead of Earnings Next Week
summary: Domino's stock is at a one-year low ahead of full-year earnings due out next week. One play is to sell short out-of-the-money (OTM) put options with a one-month expiry. It has a 2% yield for a 5% lower strike price.
